      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (normalized index of hemolysis, pressure rise) are the same as or directly mappable to the decision QoIs for worst-case operating point identification.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and modified index of hemolysis (MIH) are the primary decision QoIs. Validation data collected for the same quantities. Direct correspondence confirmed; no surrogate QoI substitution required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
